The food is good, the atmosphere convivial, and evokes the atmosphere of a British pub. BUTnot for anyone over the age of about 35.  Virtually all of the seats are very low and have no back support whatsoever.  After dining there with a friend, I required chiropractic treatment and massage therapy for the next three days to repair the damage to my back. If you are 40 years or older - "Beware The Spotted Pig"!
